Added support for unbounded pipelines and tests and fixed what we talked about regarding composites (`TextIO.Write` in the previous comments).

What the output looks like right now:

Bounded pipeline:
```java
sparkContext.parallelize(Arrays.asList(...))
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.runners.spark.examples.WordCount$ExtractWordsFn())
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.sdk.transforms.Count$PerElement$1())
.<combinePerKey>
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.runners.spark.examples.WordCount$FormatAsTextFn())
.<org.apache.beam.sdk.io.TextIO$Write$Bound>
```

Unbounded pipeline:
```java
KafkaUtils.createDirectStream(...)
.<window>
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.runners.spark.SparkNativePipelineVisitorTest$FormatKVFn())
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.sdk.transforms.Distinct$2())
.<combinePerKey>
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.sdk.transforms.Keys$1())
.mapPartitions(new org.apache.beam.sdk.transforms.WithKeys$2())
.<org.apache.beam.sdk.io.kafka.AutoValue_KafkaIO_Write>
```

Still left to do:
* Return native translations for every translation still with a `// TODO: return meaningful Spark native operation` in `TransformTranslator` and `StreamingTransformTranslator`.
* Decide if the native operation strings should be returned from `TransformEvaluator`'s `toString()` method (current implementation) or add a more binding method `toNativeString()` to its interface to make sure that nothing is forgotten in future implementations of `TransformEvaluator` resulting in parts of the debug pipeline output looking like `.TransformTranslator$123@abc12`
